00:24.625 --> 00:27.561
<i>Since the 1960s,
the port city of Montreal</i>

00:27.628 --> 00:29.729
<i>has been one of
the largest points of import</i>

00:29.797 --> 00:32.116
<i>for coke and heroin in the world.</i>

00:32.433 --> 00:35.902
<i>If you lived in New York,
or Boston, or Philly,</i>

00:35.970 --> 00:38.071
<i>anywhere in the northeast
of America really,</i>

00:38.139 --> 00:40.841
<i>and did drugs, they
came through Montreal.</i>

00:41.523 --> 00:43.210
<i>And with all that money on the table,</i>

00:43.211 --> 00:44.843
<i>everyone wanted their cut.</i>

00:45.011 --> 00:47.218
<i>So for decades, the city was at war.</i>

00:48.118 --> 00:49.953
<i>The Irish, they owned the docks,</i>

00:49.978 --> 00:52.046
<i>Haitians, well, they ran
street level operations,</i>

00:52.547 --> 00:54.314
<i>the Bikers controlled distribution,</i>

00:54.679 --> 00:56.742
<i>but they had nothing without the Mafia.</i>

00:56.951 --> 00:59.086
<i>The Mafia had those
international contacts</i>

00:59.153 --> 01:00.520
<i>to import the product.</i>

01:00.588 --> 01:03.054
<i>And in addition
to extortion and racketeering,</i>

01:03.079 --> 01:05.828
<i>they controlled the city's
construction industry as well.</i>

01:05.878 --> 01:08.437
<i>Nothing got built without their okay.</i>

01:09.263 --> 01:11.398
<i>But in the '90s, everything changed</i>

01:11.466 --> 01:14.726
<i>when Vito Rizzuto took over
from his father as mob boss.</i>

01:15.216 --> 01:17.851
<i>Vito was old school,
but he also had vision.</i>

01:18.024 --> 01:19.425
<i>He saw a different kind of future</i>

01:19.450 --> 01:21.625
<i>for his business and the city.</i>

01:28.937 --> 01:33.265
<i>And there was me, by his side
for the whole wild ride.</i>

01:33.699 --> 01:37.179
My old man put together
the bidding for that beast.

01:37.672 --> 01:39.606
Everybody shared in the bonuses,

01:39.674 --> 01:41.140
the kickbacks, the graft...

01:41.442 --> 01:42.953
It was supposed
to cost three million dollars,

01:42.977 --> 01:44.414
ended up costing a billion.

01:44.745 --> 01:47.101
Everybody should be so
lucky to get an Olympics.

01:47.195 --> 01:49.382
There he is, man of the hour.

01:49.450 --> 01:50.850
Hey! They all behavin' themselves?

01:50.918 --> 01:52.819
No one shot anyone yet,
so that's a good start.

01:52.887 --> 01:53.906
It's good.

01:53.931 --> 01:56.179
Everyone! Everyone!

01:56.757 --> 01:59.125
I know you're all interested
to hear what Vito has to say,

01:59.193 --> 02:00.710
so I'm gonna let him get to it.

02:01.466 --> 02:02.554
Gentlemen!

02:03.064 --> 02:04.828
We are all at war.

02:05.466 --> 02:07.562
Jacques, you and I still do
some business, but

02:07.768 --> 02:10.002
you still try to get
my action on the east end.

02:10.071 --> 02:12.172
Papa Lou, you and the Irish,

02:12.270 --> 02:13.906
been spilling blood for a year.

02:15.309 --> 02:16.890
This is our city.

02:17.411 --> 02:20.578
We got to acknowledge
that nobody is going anywhere.

02:20.992 --> 02:22.582
All right, so, question is,

02:22.650 --> 02:25.078
do you wanna keep fighting
over street corners,

02:25.228 --> 02:27.265
or do you want a piece
of all the action?

02:28.789 --> 02:31.703
Now, what I'm proposing
is a cooperative.

02:33.127 --> 02:35.779
You're all here for a specific reason,

02:35.804 --> 02:38.500
'cause of what you bring to the table.

02:39.501 --> 02:42.242
But we gotta conduct this
like a business.

02:43.406 --> 02:44.873
You all get a say,

02:45.973 --> 02:47.774
but there can only be one CEO.

02:48.709 --> 02:50.110
I suppose that's you?

02:50.177 --> 02:51.411
Yeah.

02:51.479 --> 02:54.280
Because I own something
that none of you do.

02:54.348 --> 02:56.500
City Hall and the cops.

02:57.724 --> 02:59.210
But I'm willing to share.

03:01.455 --> 03:02.756
Keep talking.

03:02.823 --> 03:06.960
Look, there's enough coke,
hash, hookers, gambling

03:07.027 --> 03:10.897
for all of us to make a lot
of money if we work together.

03:12.099 --> 03:13.492
But if we don't,

03:14.273 --> 03:16.967
we're gonna end up in prison or dead.

03:18.205 --> 03:20.781
So here's what I propose,
you all go home.

03:21.142 --> 03:22.275
You relax.

03:22.343 --> 03:23.656
You drink a beer

03:23.878 --> 03:26.015
and you think about your bright future.

03:26.689 --> 03:27.789
What do you say?

03:29.417 --> 03:32.919
<i>And so began one of
the greatest runs ever.</i>

03:32.987 --> 03:35.855
<i>What we did should be studied
in history books.</i>

03:35.923 --> 03:37.398
<i>I'm not kidding.</i>

03:37.558 --> 03:39.392
<i>We brought peace between people</i>

03:39.460 --> 03:42.195
<i>who would never have walked
down the same block together.</i>

03:42.263 --> 03:43.496
<i>Like ever.</i>

03:43.564 --> 03:45.765
<i>Between the gang syndicate we created,</i>

03:45.833 --> 03:49.250
<i>and the politicians
and the cops in our pockets,</i>

03:49.516 --> 03:50.960
<i>we were unstoppable.</i>

03:51.050 --> 03:53.752
<i>Life was good.
Life was good for everyone.</i>

03:54.008 --> 03:56.531
<i>But if there's one thing
you can ever count on,</i>

03:56.750 --> 03:59.345
<i>it's that gangsters
are greedy, petty asses,</i>

03:59.679 --> 04:03.226
<i>and will always screw things up.</i>

